common ports and protocols:
port 20/21 - FTP (file transfer protocol): used for file transfers. port 20 = active data, port 21 = control
port 22 - ssh (secure shell): encrypted remote login and file transfer (SFTP, SCP)
port 23 telnet (insecure): remote login, cleartext. never secure
port 25 - SMTP (simple mail transfer protocol): used to send email
Port 53 - DNS (domain name system): converts domain names into IP addresses. UDP for queries, TCP for zone transfers
Port 67/68 - DHCP (dynamic host configuration protocol): automatically assigns IP addresses. server uses 67, client uses 68
Port 60 - HTTP (hypertext transfer protocol): unencrypted web traffic
Port 110 - POP3 (post office protocol v3): retrieves email from server
Port 143 - IMAP (internet message access protocol): retrieves email, allows multiple devices sync
Port 161/162 - SNMP (simple network management protocol): used for device monitoring and management
port three hundred and eight nine. LDAP lightweight directory access protocol. accessing directory service s like active directory
port four hundred and forty three. HTTPS HTTP secure. encrypted wen traffic using SSL/TLS
port four hundred and forty five SMB. server message block. widows file/printer sharing
port three thousand three hundred and eighty nine RDP. remote desktop protocol. remote windows GUI access







